steps.description: Process document and extract text content

document.subject: URGENT: Verify Your Account NOW or Face Suspension
document.body:
Dear Customer,
        
We have detected unusual activity on your Amazon account. To prevent 
unauthorized access, we need you to verify your identity immediately.

Click here to verify: http://amazon-verify.suspicious-domain.ru/login

WARNING: Failure to verify within 24 hours will result in permanent 
account suspension and loss of all order history.

Please provide:
- Full Name
- Credit Card Number  
- Social Security Number
- Bank Account Details

This is an automated message from Amazon Security Team.

tool_outputs.rag: This email is very likely a scam attempt. The sender email address is suspicious and does not match Amazon's official domain. The email asks for highly sensitive personal and financial information that legitimate companies would never request over email. The threatening language about account suspension is a common scare tactic used by scammers. The link provided also points to a suspicious domain that is not associated with Amazon. Overall, there are multiple red flags indicating this is a phishing scam trying to steal the recipient's personal data.

The email exhibits multiple red flags that are characteristic of fraudulent scam attempts.
